Three persons have been abducted by gunmen at the Ikakumo area of Ondo state. The victims were said to be travellers. Ikakumo, a border town with Edo state, is in Akoko North East local government area. Witnesses said a commercial motorcyclist drove into the scene and was beaten to coma by the suspects. He was said to have reported the abduction to local residents. Police Area Commander , Assistant Commissioner of Police, Razak Rauf, who confirmed the incident said investigation has begun on the case. Ondo Police spokesman, ASP Tee-Leo Ikoro, said he was yet to be briefed on the incident.